<TEXT>
a local prosecutor monday declared 
obscene the sexually explict as nasty as they wanna be album by 
rap group 2 live crew and banned its sale in pickens and 
greenville counties 
the album also has been declared obscene by a federal judge in 
florida and san antonio texas store owners pulled it from 
shelves last week after they were threatened with arrest in 
sacramento calif the district attorney monday refused to 
prosecute merchants selling the album 
stores will be sent letters about the ruling and must clear the 
album off their shelves by june 26 or risk arrest said prosecutor 
joseph j watson 
the whole purpose of the lyrics is to appeal to the prurient 
interest of sex they are patently offensive and they are utterly 
without any serious artistic or literary value said watson 
summing up the state laws threepart test of obscenity its 
filth 
sale of the album is now banned in communities that comprise 
onefifth of the states residents on thursday the album was 
declared obscene and its sale prohibited in richland county 
anyone found guilty of selling obscene material to a minor faces 
a maximum of five years in prison and a 5000 fine the penalty 
for selling to an adult is up to three years in prison and a 3000 
fine 
to get a conviction a prosecutor would have to convince a jury 
the album is obscene 
debbie bennett spokeswoman for 2 live crews label luke 
records wondered whether watson would now look at other material 
being sold 
i hope this means theyre also taking out all the xrated 
movies and all the other albums on major labels that have all the 
same language as 2 live crew ms bennett said in a telephone 
interview from miami 
i hope theyre not limiting it to a relatively obscure black 
group and an even more obscure black label 
she said more than 17 million copies of the album have been 
sold 
sacramento district attorney steve white monday rejected 
requests to prosecute merchants who sell the album saying it was 
extraordinarily crude and offensive but did not violate state 
obscenity law 
to be legally obscene a work must appeal to prurient 
interest describe sexual conduct in a patently offensive way and 
taken as a whole lack serious literary artistic political or 
scientific value as judged against a contemporary statewide 
standard white said in a statement 
meanwhile in tennessee acuffrose music inc sued 2 live crew 
in federal court saying the group wasnt authorized to record a 
song derived from the roy orbison hit oh pretty woman 
acuffrose seeks unspecified damages and forfeiture of all 
copies of the groups as clean as they wanna be album the less 
explicit version of the one at the center of the obscenity 
controversy because it contains a rap version of the orbison hit 
</TEXT>
