died at devonshire hospital in london said katherine morgan a 
relative 
born in oldham lancashire miss turner joined the royal carl 
rosa opera company in london in 1916 she made her debut a year 
later as a page in wagners tannhaeuser and rapidly took on 
lead roles in productions of tosca aida and madama 
butterfly 
