in wagners das rheingold 
from 1950 to 1959 she was a professor of voice at the university 
of oklahoma she returned to london and taught voice at the royal 
academy of music until 1966 
she was made a dame commander of the order of the british empire 
in 1962 and was awarded honorary doctorates of music by manchester 
and oxford universities 
