ready to help once the oil comes ashore 
salvage crews working on the norwegian tanker sunday began 
transferring oil from a leaking cargo bin to another holding tank 
aboard the vessel cutting off the flow of oil into the water 
the ship has definitely quit leaking sedwick said a 
reconnaissance crew flew over at 6 this morning and didnt find any 
oil within 5 miles of the ship thats a pretty good indication 
that theyve stopped the leak 
he said crews from smit america salvage inc also began pumping 
water out of another holding tank that had become flooded during 
firefighting efforts once the oil transfer and the water release 
are complete sedwick said crews will decide when to begin moving 
the remainder of the ships 38 milliongallon cargo to a smaller 
vessel a process called lightering he expected that to begin 
monday 
on saturday crews had continued dousing the hull of the mega 
borg with cooling water so it would not reignite when the oil 
transfers began sedwick said sunday officials believed there was 
no longer a threat of a reflash 
divers attempting to rescue five loggerhead sea turtles spotted 
