from the antiabortion stance said richard e ryan senior vice 
president of the texasbased polling company tarrance amp associates 
but he questioned the surveys validity 
even though about 60 percent of those polled tend to favor 
allowing abortion some 50 percent to 60 percent also tend to favor 
placing some controls on abortion ryan said 
they are the mushy middle he said they want to have 
their cake and eat it too 
