the magazine reported in its june 25 issue which goes on sale 
today 
as many as 60 percent of the 347 us soldiers wounded in the 
dec 20 attack were probably hit by fire from their comrades and 
nine were killed by other american servicemen newsweek said 
citing unidentified military sources 
we just dont have any comment on that at this time said 
pentagon spokesman ken satterfield 
