owner named as a plaintiff in the classaction lawsuit said the 
state wants to further regulate a procedure that already is safe 
and protected as a fundamental privacy right 
there is no justification for changing the injunction mainly 
because the safety of abortion has not declined since 1982 
carres said last week citing the states own statistics that 
firsttrimester abortions are far safer than childbirth 
while a single abortionrelated death is recorded every few 
years she said anywhere from 15 to 23 childbirthrelated deaths 
