<TEXT>
president bush on monday announced his 
longdelayed selection of a new director for the office of 
government ethics naming washington dc lawyer stephen d potts 
potts 59 would succeed frank q nebeker a holdover appointee 
the ethics office reviews all personal financial filings of 
federal officials and interprets laws and regulations relating to 
conflicts of interest 
during his presidential campaign bush vowed to enhance and 
expand the powers of the office and to appoint a senior 
counsellor to the president 
even so the post has remained under interim management through 
the 17 months of bushs presidency 
his first choice for the job paul pressler of houston a 
fundamentalist religious leader was withdrawn from consideration 
after a routine fbi check uncovered what white house aides at the 
time called an ethics problem 
potts has been a partner with the law firm of shaw pittman 
potts and trowbridge since 1961 
a native of memphis and graduate of vanderbilt university potts 
is a former vice president of the cherokee life insurance co in 
nashville tenn 
a white house fact sheet on potts also notes that mr potts 
has won five national fatherson tennis championships 
