india and pakistan both claim kashmir a predominately moslem 
state that joined mainly hindu india when britain partitioned the 
subcontinent along religious lines in 1947 
india and pakistan fought wars over kashmir in 1948 and 1965 
the territory is now divided by a ceasefire line and the armies 
of both countries have massed troops and artillery along the border 
india accuses pakistan of arming and training moslem kashmiri 
militants who are fighting for independence from india 
pakistan denies the charges but supports the uprising on the 
indian side of the ceasefire line calling it a movement for 
selfdetermination 
an indian official said the new governmentinexile could 
endanger the planned talks 
it is certainly not going to help pakistan or relations 
and i hope it has not derailed this process of opening talks 
said one senior official at the indian high commission the embassy 
in islamabad he spoke on condition of anonymity 
