<TEXT>
john s niederhauser dubbed mr 
potato for his work developing a blightresistant strain of 
spuds won the 200000 world food prize on monday 
niederhausers work increased potato harvests and helped prevent 
famine in developing nations said norman borlaug founder of the 
prize 
his achievements toward developing a blightresistant potato 
variety have affected countries from mexico to bangladesh 
borlaug said without a doubt dr niederhausers discoveries 
have had a dramatic impact on the fooddeficient regions of the 
world 
the world food prize rewards research in production or 
distribution of food niederhauser is the fourth recipient 
niederhauser worked for a private agricultural research 
foundation in mexico and by 1982 was working with a similar group 
in poland 
he developed a strain of potato resistant to late blight 
disease the disease blamed for the great potato famine that 
devastated ireland and other european countries about a century ago 
niederhauser also works as a consultant for biosphere ii a 
research program developing a sealed food production environment 
that could be selfsustaining 
the challenge is enormous niederhauser said by 2010 if 
there is a trip to mars the crew using some of the technology 
developed in the biosphere ii could produce their own food en 
route and eliminate one of the major limiting factors of such a 
trip 
borlaug won the 1970 nobel peace prize for his research 
fostering the green revolution in developing nations the world 
food prize is funded by private donors 
</TEXT>
