sentencing for richard c johnson 41 of nashua nh martin 
quigley 27 of dundalk ireland and christina l reid 25 a 
computer technician from sunnyvale calif 
the trio was convicted on a range of charges including 
conspiracy to violate the federal arms export act and to injure or 
destroy property belonging to the united kingdom possessing 
property to aid foreign insurgents and aiding an insurgent group 
in violation of us laws said mazzones clerk deborah whitney 
a fourth defendant gerald hoy of easton pa pleaded guilty 
last week a fifth peter e maguire is a fugitive believed to be 
in ireland 
johnson faces a maximum sentence of 28 years quigley 18 years 
and reid and hoy 8 years apiece 
