a california man who has become the first person 
to bicycle any substantial distance along the great wall set out 
monday for the final leg of his 1255mile journey 
kevin foster 30 has already peddled 1065 miles and said hes 
having the best time i ever had 
foster left monday from mutianyu northeast of beijing for the 
final 190 miles of his adventure mutianyu about 42 miles from the 
capital is marked by steep mountains and rugged terrain 
foster said he plans to reach the eastern end of the great wall 
which chinas emperors originally built more than 2000 years ago 
to keep out foreigners at shanhaiguan pass on the bohai sea by 
about june 27 
it took foster a parttime actor from ojai calif years of 
effort to win chinese government approval for his trip which began 
may 11 at the walls westernmost pass jiayuguan about 950 miles 
from beijing 
the project bogged down for more than a week when the jeep that 
was to accompany him failed to show up and he was forced to fly 
back to the capital 
he started again on may 28 and cycled until june 8 when he had 
to travel by jeep and train to beijing to avoid passing through a 
closed military area 
foster said of the 1065 miles hes ridden in 19 days 
threefourths of that has been on top of the wall in some places 
the wall disintegrated into rubble or disappeared altogether and 
he bicycled in its traces 
he has been accompanied by a driver and jeep carrying supplies 
and two young chinese staffers from his host organization the 
institute of geography who have taken turns cyling with him 
the group spent some nights in small towns that hundreds of 
years ago housed soldiers guarding the frontier other nights they 
slept on the wall sometimes finding families living in the towers 
of the wall 
he said the best part was watching the sun set on the gobi 
desert after a days cycling 
the sand the stars the cool breeze on a tower thats over 
1000 years old thats what its all about 
