trevor pinnocks tasty rendition of henry purcells festival 
odes is among those compelling recordings that sing buy me 
when played in a record shop 
the precision and vigor of the perfomances and the clarity and 
immediacy of the recording are instantly impressive surely 
however this owes something to the composers skills 
the first and best known of the odes come ye sons of art 
was prepared for the birthday of queen mary ii in 1694 welcome 
to all the pleasures was written in honor of the patron of music 
for st cecilias day in 1683 while of old when heroes thought 
it base was composed for some municipal bash in yorkshire in 1690 
the music has all the gravity splendor and gaiety of a royal 
court thought the words be as empty as many a crowned head 
consider this from the first ode 
strike the viol touch the lute 
wake the harp inspire the flute 
sing your patronesses praise 
in cheerful and harmonious lays 
