the museum of fine arts in houston opened a major retrospective 
of the graphic art of jasper johns 
jasper johns printed symbols features over 150 prints 
illustrated books sculpture and proofs 
he used printmaking to map out new territory exploiting the 
nuances of repetition to challenge our notions of creativity 
said alison de lima greene associate curator of 20th century art 
at the museum 
johns created his first lithograph in 1960 his first print 
target was created in 1960 after he was given two lithograph 
stones by the founder of universal limited art editions 
over the next decade johns created a large number of prints at 
universal including his celebrated lithographs based on the 
numerals zero through nine 
