<TEXT>
the nations savings and loan disaster finally 
exploded on capitol hill as a political issue after a freshman 
republican lawmaker provided the spark 
congress has been wrestling with the problem since the sampl 
industrys governmentbacked insurance fund went belly up at the 
end of the reagan administration tens of billions of dollars are 
being spent to bail out close down and sell off thrift 
institutions 
though costly it seemed for the longest time that president 
bushs effort to keep the issue quiet was the best strategy 
oh sure its expensive the white house said but lets keep it 
off the books not count it against our deficitreduction efforts 
remember that a lot of it is just working capital 
congress unable to find a good alternative went along 
although trouble flared up sporadically for some lawmakers 
a handful of senators the socalled keating five are under 
investigation because of their extraordinary efforts on behalf of 
one spectacularly failed thrift some house members seeking 
reelection his year are under attack for their ties to financial 
institutions 
but for the most part lawmakers who werent personally involved 
in the issue appeared to be standing back 
then this spring something changed and the issue seemed to 
reach critical mass 
perhaps it was the nearness of the elections theres a chance 
it was the cumulative effect of neverending bad news and 
escalating costs 
and just maybe the public began to catch on that whatever the 
bookkeeping tricks more of their federal tax dollars would be 
going to bail out inept or crooked thrift operations than say to 
education 
enter peter smith a firstterm republican congressman from 
vermont who reached the house in a threeway race where the 
democrat and a socialist split the majority of the vote 
i basically blew my stack smith says 
two weeks ago smith introduced a resolution in the house calling 
for the appointment of a special prosecutor known officially as an 
independent counsel to go after the savings and loans 
the measure would have no binding effect and in some ways is 
flawed an independent counsel can be requested simply by a 
majority of either the republicans or the democrats on the 
congressional judiciary committees 
but a freshman doesnt move the committee structure smith 
said 
and the purpose of the law is to address conflicts of interest 
the justice department would have investigating the bush 
administration not to balkanize federal enforcement efforts for 
every issue that comes along 
when youre talking about congress and highranking government 
officials i think the conflict exists smith said 
his resolution immediately touched off lawmakers starving for a 
way to look tough on the issue by late last week more than 170 
house members were cosponsoring his resolution 
even though the resolution could rightly be seen as a vote of no 
confidence in the administration and especially attorney general 
dick thornburgh republicans were embracing smith as a hero 
my sense is the justice department has moved slowly if my 
resolution has something to do with prodding those people then i 
think its a good thing smith said im just sorry it took so 
long 
when smith scheduled a news conference on his resolution last 
week he expected three colleagues to join him instead 17 showed 
up among them house minority whip newt gingrich rga a top 
backer of the reagan administrations sampl deregulation that 
democrats say led to the financial disaster 
whether or not a special prosecutor is appointed it now appears 
clear that congress will take some sort of action this year 
savings and loan operators now are rivaling drug dealers as 
congress glamour criminals 
top democrats and republicans on the house banking committee 
last week introduced legislation to bolster justice department 
enforcement and give the federal government new powers to chase 
down some of the money embezzled from the savings institutions 
senate judiciary committee chairman joseph biden ddel 
announced a crackdown bill of his own and attacked the 
administration for cutting back the fbis budget request for 
hundreds of new agents for the crisis 
i have succeeded beyond my wildest dreams smith said 
