new jersey casino licenses 
banking sources familiar with the talks said last week that 
trumps four major bank lenders citibank bank trust new york 
corp chase manhattan and manufactueres hanover agreed to 
provide an additional 60 million in loans and to temporarily 
suspend interest payments 
the sources had said citicorp and bankers trust would provide 
about twothirds of the new loan 
the big banks have been trying to persuade some of the smaller 
creditors including some japanese banks to go along with the 
proposed restructuring but some of those institutions have been 
opposed to the plan first fidelity bancorp of newark nj and 
midlantic banks inc of edison nj reportedly were the main 
holdouts 
the ongoing negotiations also have raised speculation that 
bankers want more authority over operation of trumps properties 
the wall street journal reported today that the banks have been 
demanding that trump appoint two top executives a chief executive 
officer and a chief financial officer to control the daily 
operations of the trump organization dan klores a spokesman for 
trump refused to comment on the negotiations or the reports 
he said the banks resumed talks today after their meeting broke 
off on saturday banks also have refused official comment 
at his 44th birthday celebration at his taj mahal casino resort 
on saturday trump told throngs of employees that he was confident 
he would rise above his financial problems 
over the years ive surprised a lot of people the largest 
surprise is yet to come he said 
the purpose behind the proposed debt restructuring plan was to 
give trump time to wait for his assets to rise in value 
trump has been beset by a slumping real estate market in new 
york and disappointing results from his three atlantic city 
casinos and the trump shuttle airline 
his real estate holdings which also include new yorks plaza 
hotel and trump tower were built largely with the funds from bank 
loans and borrowed from junk bonds trump owes banks an estimated 
2 billion and bondholders another 1 billion 
</TEXT>
