<DOCNO> AP900618-0222 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
sixteen years ago the chairman tried to tame 
inflation once and for all with a whip as a member of president 
fords administration he helped launch a campaign to whip 
inflation now 
now critics say he is using the same rope in another way to 
tie up the economy 
to a very limited extent in the 1970s it might be claimed the 
chairman succeeded whereas consumer prices had risen 11 percent in 
1974 the increase had dropped to as low as 58 percent in 1976 
not everyone then was willing to credit the chairman with having 
succeeded because the campaign was atrociously planned it was 
launched as the economy was plunging into a recession that would 
relieve pressure on prices 
and critics today are wondering again if something of the sort 
might be occurring once again the enemy is inflation or the 
threat of it the goal is to destroy it and the risk is a descent 
into recession 
as before the chairman is the same in 1974 alan greenspan was 
chairman of the presidents council of economic advisers in 1990 
he is chairman of the federal reserve board which seeks to control 
the money supply 
greenspan has a firm almost unrelenting grip on it and perhaps 
as a direct result you cant buy and spend if you havent got 
access to funds there is growing evidence of an economy 
progressively weakening 
consumer demand has shrunk real estate sales and building have 
almost stopped in some areas small businesses especially those 
related in any way to real estate have trouble borrowing 
corporate profits are on the skids 
the evidence shows up all over plans for investment in new 
plants and equipment have ceased to grow and privatesector 
employment shows signs of shriveling even when temporary census 
bureau jobs are included 
money is the raw material that powers economic activity and 
when the fed tightens the spigot the wheels of commerce slows 
keep the spigot closed long enough and some of the wheels stop 
eventually recession threatens 
some economists think that recession is closing in and that 
statistics released over the next month might even show it but 
there seems to be no letup in the chairmans resolve to lick this 
monster called inflation 
whether he has the right notion or is destined to badly damage 
the economy is up for debate greenspan has his supporters even 
among business people who say the nation can never embark on a 
real expansion until the job is done 
that job of course is to bury inflation so deeply it cannot 
arise again for years 
the chairmans first effort failed after a few years after 
dropping to 58 percent in 1976 the consumer price index reached 
double digits in 1979 and helped bring on the deep recession of 
1981 and 1982 
recovery followed helped a great deal by a loosening of the 
money spigot as most people know because they benefited from it 
the economy began a long expansion right through 1989 an expansion 
that might be about to end 
beginning late in the 1980s the fed once again began closing 
the spigot not abruptly or completely but enough to reduce the 
growth of bank reserves which govern lending and then to bring 
about an actual contraction 
now the signs of a economy on the edge are showing up 
everywhere and from everywhere the cries for easier money will be 
heard not just from business either but from elected officials 
who fear for their jobs 
greenspans supporters and probably the chairman himself seem 
to think however that slow growth or even a recession might be 
the price to pay to bury inflation for years to come 
</TEXT>
