federal reserve board the letters were obtained by the associated 
press by sources in the house 
in one letter wirth said wise was not only qualified but his 
experience with the thrift industry and housing will add valuable 
perspective to the councils deliberations on consumer and 
community affairs 
the other letter was handwritten by wirth to volcker he is 
extremely able and would be an excellent appointment wirth said 
of wise 
wise was not named to the feds consumer advisory council but 
he was put on the feds thrift institutions advisory council in 
1985 he served on the citizens advisory group for three years 
culminating as the president in 1987 
the group meets four times a year with the feds board of 
governors to discuss developments in the thrift industry 
