<TEXT>
boeing 737 jetliners are now being produced at a 
rate of 17 a month boeing commercial airplane group said monday 
the company said in a news release that it had met its 
previously announced goal of increased production for the small 
twinjet up from 14 per month earlier this year 
boeing which has a backlog of 1750 passenger jets has been 
increasing production rates throughout its product line production 
of 747s went from twoandahalf per month to five a month last 
year while 757 production went from five to seven planes a month 
and 767s went from four to five in early 1990 
boeing plans to produce 382 jetliners including five 707s for 
military use in 1990 up from 284 in 1989 the company was hit by 
a 48day machinists strike last year which effectively halted 
production 
