<TEXT>
japan and the united states have a long way to 
go to improve trade relations but some us companies are 
succeeding in the japanese marketplace us trade representative 
carla a hills said monday 
japan is not a completely closed society and the united states 
isnt a collection of uncompetitive failing industries hills 
said at the annual dinner of the japan society 
hills said us exports to japan last year were greater than our 
exports to west germany france and italy combined since 1986 she 
said japan has increased its imports from all nations 64 percent 
however she said the problem is that japan should be doing 
more the united states should be doing more 
our entrepreneurs must be permitted to trade and invest in 
japan as freely as japanese entrepreneurs are able to trade and 
invest here in the united states she said 
the american people will not be satisfied until all american 
businesses can offer their goods and services in japan in free and 
open competition 
she said us companies face obstacles in trying to market 
products in japan in the areas of digital computer networks 
telecommunications auto parts semiconductors and construction 
mrs hills noted that a us company motorola two weeks ago 
beat out seven companies from japan the united states and europe 
in a contest to set standards for japans next generation of 
digital cellular telephones 
unfortunately she said under the rules of the competition 
motorola must publish the design of its winning system and must 
license other companies in japan free of charge the united 
states wants assurances that motorola will be allowed to market its 
system and win a piece of the digital cellular market in japan 
the dinner was given in honor of japans influential film maker 
akira kurosawa who won the 1990 japan society award for increasing 
appreciation and understanding of japanese society and culture 
the japan society is a private nonprofit organization devoted 
to cultural educational and public affairs and improving 
usjapan relations 
