prospects for interest rate cuts dealers said 
traders believe the federal reserve which sets the nations 
monetary policy is more likely to nudge interest rates lower to 
stimulate the economy amid signs of a slowdown such a move would 
be bearish for the dollar which is more attractive to investors 
when us rates are higher 
jerry rothman a trader with merrill lynch futures said there 
was no news to affect the dollar and that investors were testing 
the us currency to see how far it will go 
